  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Uncertainty quantification was performed across material property and geometric tolerance inputs; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to rank input variability contributors, and the results informed the UQ sampling strategy. The dominant drivers identified in that screening exercise (titanium alloy elastic modulus, screw-rod interface friction coefficient, and vertebral body surrogate stiffness) were found to contribute jointly to approximately 78% of the output variance in yield force prediction. These findings are summarised narratively in the UQ report (Doc. FEA-UQ-2024-003) but have not been encoded as a structured hasSensitivityAnalysis artefact in this credibility package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "modelRiskLevel": 3,
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
